nodes.title: Standalone MM-Audio - generate audio for existing video
widgets_values:
Since MMAudio can use up to 5GB of VRAM, you may be limited with video length or quality using MMaudio Generation as part of the Main Workflow.
This stand-alone version allows you to generate higher quality or longer videos using the main workflow then add audio later.

Load your silent video into this plugin, and add audio in post production. You can try different seeds and prompts to get the best audio for the video you produced.  

* A blank prompt will work fine, however you can also use the prompt to better describe the scene and add details around the sounds that wouldn't be detected by the plug-in nornally. for example, you can hear birds chirping in the background, the sound sound of a waterfall and leaves rustling in the background. Nightclub scene with dance music playing in the background, the crowd is cheering loudly.

DISABLE all "Main Render Groups" in Control Control Panel when using this standalone plug-in.

nodes.title: Using the workflow - Important Read
widgets_values:
T2V Main Workflow - recommended method 2-stages:
- Select T2V Model in control Panel
- Choose a LQ light blue resolution in resolution selector - don't worry about the low res it will quadruple in the final render.
- Enable 1a, 2, 3, 4, 5 in the control panel 
- Set Stage 1 steps to 14 (default), Set STage 2 steps to 25 or higher (default)
1) Stage 1 - Low res preview render - you will see a preview render that will show you your prompt, loras are working
2) It will pause and let you decide if you want to continue, or cancel and try again.
3) Stage 2 - Takes your preview render as input and Double the resolution for a high quality intermediate render
4) Upscaling - It will now take your Intermediate render and double the resolution again.
5) Interpolation - It will double your framerate.

I2V recommended method 1-stage:
- Select I2V Model in Control Panel
- Choose a Dark Purple (I2V) resolution. Or use  custom known working I2V Resolution. * important or you will get artifacts and color blotches
- Enable 1b, 2, 4, 5 in the control panel (skipping 3)
- Set the Steps to 25 or higher in the I2V section of the workflow.  
- You have the option to use the original img resolution, using the scaled resolution of the input video if it isn't an support resolution it might not work
1) Stage 1 - It will do a 1-pass full render at your selected steps and selected resolution
2) It will pause and let you decide if you want to continue to the upscaler, or cancel and try again
3) Upscaling - It will now take your Intermediate render and double the resolution.
4) Interpolation - It will double your framerate.

Video Extention:
- Select I2V Model in Control Panel
- Choose a Dark Purple (I2V) resolution or use the original resolution of the video.  This process uses the I2V Model so resolution is important
- Enable 1d, 2,4,5 in the control panel (skipping 3)
- Its very important to use a low or mid-resolution input source at this point, or you will run out of memory. 
- Use an intermediate render from the T2V 2-stage or manually set a low to medium resolution for your video - you can set this manually.  Alternatively you can choose to use the original video resolution.   If you are using an intermediate source or the intermediate render from the T2V 2-stage method, this will work perfectly.. its designed for this.
- Select if you want to just render out the extended part or the full combined video.. Select True if you want the full combined video.  This will also pass the entire fully combined video to the next step the upscaler.  This is why its important to use an intermediate level video, as it will upscale and interpolate again.

1) Stage 1 - It will do a 1-pass full render at your selected steps and selected resolution
2) It will pause and let you decide if you want to continue to the upscaler, or cancel and try again
3) Upscaling - It will now take your Intermediate render and double the resolution.
4) Interpolation - It will double your framerate.

- Prompting with Wildcard Capabilities
